id: pm-3hps
title: "Context relevance signal feature store: derived recency, graph, claim, risk, deadline, knowledge-density, and semantic-match signals"
description: Build the SDK-facing derived signal layer that feeds adaptive context ranking without scanning every item file.
type: Task
status: closed
priority: 1
tags[4]: "area:sdk",context,relevance,scale
created_at: "2026-07-06T23:50:39.057Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-22T06:29:03.376Z"
closed_at: "2026-07-22T06:29:02.722Z"
author: codex-agent
estimated_minutes: 360
acceptance_criteria: "SDK exposes stable signal extraction primitives; signals cover recency/activity density, dependency proximity, claim/focus state, priority/risk/deadline pressure, knowledge density, author affinity, and semantic similarity; feature reads are index-backed via pm-801d; signal snapshots are deterministic for a fixed workspace; missing optional indexes degrade gracefully with explicit metadata."
parent: pm-4k6b
risk: medium
confidence: medium
resolution: Implemented and verified the SDK-facing derived signal layer across pm context and pm next.
expected_result: Context and next consume deterministic index-backed signals with explicit fallback provenance and bounded ranking output.
actual_result: "CLI, SDK, and MCP contracts consume cursor-bound stable snapshots with per-read dynamic overlays; packed consumer, scale, quality, and exact coverage gates pass."
