comments[18]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-06T23:50:39.057Z",codex-agent,"Duplicate check: searched all statuses for context relevance scorer/signal extraction/feature store; only parent pm-4k6b and historical search-ranking work matched, so this is the non-duplicate signal-layer implementation slice."
  "2026-07-21T16:59:24.487Z",codex-derived-context-20260721,"Implementation tranche 2026-07-21: added public ContextSignalStore and pluggable adapter contracts, a same-directory atomic JSON adapter, format_version + signal_set_version envelopes, caller-supplied authoritative source cursors, deterministic id-sorted rows, strict untrusted snapshot validation, and self-healing missing/stale/corrupt rebuilds. buildItemContextRelevanceCandidates now accepts index-derived activity, graph, claim/focus, knowledge, and author maps while preserving metadata fallbacks plus usage and semantic signals. The store joins persisted signals back to authoritative item objects and explicitly reports fresh/rebuilt plus degradation warnings."
  "2026-07-21T17:15:35.002Z",codex-derived-context-20260721,"Verification evidence 2026-07-21: strict release gates pass end to end. Full suite: 333 files / 6,067 tests / exact 100% statements (40,824/40,824), branches (28,712/28,712), functions (8,299/8,299), and lines (39,711/39,711). Build, typecheck, docs, docstrings, static quality, package boundary, token gate, version policy, secret scan, 13-package npx smoke, 88-command package-first dogfood, npm pack, published-version compatibility, Sentry, and telemetry all pass. Manual packed consumer independently proved rebuilt->fresh snapshot reuse and compact create output."
  "2026-07-21T17:25:36.684Z",codex-derived-context-20260721,"PR #633 review round 1: accepted Gemini threads 3624227238 and 3624227250. Replaced the multi-pass filter/map/Set assignee precomputation with a no-author Symbol sentinel plus inline single-pass comparison, and removed the redundant copied array before authoritative-id sorting. Focused tests pass 17/17; typecheck, ESLint complexity, zero-clone duplication, 100% docstrings, package boundary, and token-budget gates pass. CodSpeed's reported regressions are 0% to -0.01% on untouched benchmark surfaces and are classified as simulation noise; five untouched benchmarks moved positively by the same range."
  "2026-07-21T17:38:49.529Z",codex-derived-context-20260721,"PR #633 CI follow-up: coverage shard 1/4 exposed a defensive-runtime input where assignee was non-string; context relevance called trim() directly. Replaced direct normalization with a typed scalar normalizer using distinct missing-value sentinels, preserving author/assignee semantics and the prior single-pass allocation optimization. Focused context relevance and command tests pass, full lint/typecheck pass, and the exact GitHub blob coverage shard command now exits 0."
  "2026-07-21T17:46:06.647Z",codex-derived-context-20260721,"PR #633 Gemini round 2: accepted three boundary-hardening findings for the untrusted snapshot and filesystem adapter contracts. Added failing tests first for whitespace-only source cursors, whitespace-only item ids, and non-string runtime adapter paths; then implemented trim-aware rejection and typeof guarding. Focused suite passes 21/21, typecheck passes, and full lint/static/docstring/package/token gates pass."
  "2026-07-21T17:50:54.210Z",codex-derived-context-20260721,"PR #633 exact-head closeout: feature-store primitives, defensive validation, index-signal injection, atomic adapter, recovery diagnostics, TDD review fixes, installed-package proof, and all repository gates are green at 90ef2974. The canonical item remains open because CLI context/next integration and continuously folded write-path signals are later scope. CodeRabbit's non-code status is externally rate-limited; Gemini findings were fully resolved."
  "2026-07-21T17:57:55.651Z",codex-derived-context-20260721,"PR #633 Gemini round 3: accepted graceful degradation for derived-cache write failures and whitespace-only actor normalization. Added failing tests first; rebuilt candidates now remain available with context_signal_store_write_failed, and blank author/assignee values map to distinct missing sentinels without false affinity. Preserved non-string dirty-metadata tolerance instead of adopting a throwing helper because context reads must degrade safely. Focused tests pass 22/22; typecheck, lint, zero-clone, 100% docstrings, package boundary, token, docs, and links gates pass."
  "2026-07-21T18:09:46.980Z",codex-derived-context-20260721,"PR #633 final paginated review: accepted Gemini sourceCursor runtime guard finding. Added regression coverage for null-as-runtime input and now reject non-string cursors with the documented TypeError before trim. Focused test and typecheck pass."
  "2026-07-22T05:00:38.913Z",codex-root-20260722,"Implementation start 2026-07-22: actively deliver the shared index-backed adaptive-context acceptance surface across pm-4k6b, pm-3hps, and pm-801d. Scope is CLI/SDK context and next integration, continuously maintained derived signals, deterministic explainability, bounded token packing, and scan-fallback parity. All-status duplicate review reused this canonical three-item lineage; no parallel context item was created."
  "2026-07-22T05:15:05.199Z",codex-root-20260722,"Progress evidence 2026-07-22: the signal store now persists only caller-independent metadata features, overlays author/time/usage inputs on every read, derives normalized activity and graph signals, automatically binds to the effective metadata-index cursor, and degrades to deterministic scan cursors."
  "2026-07-22T05:38:56.331Z",codex-root-20260722,"Verification evidence 2026-07-22: full all-source suite passes 335 files / 6,079 tests with exact 100% statements (41,093/41,093), branches (28,937/28,937), functions (8,343/8,343), and lines (39,966/39,966). Typecheck, ESLint, zero-clone duplication, 100% docstrings/static quality, SDK boundary, token budget, contracts, docs links, context-eval, secret scan, npm audit, 13-package packed smoke, and 88-command package-first dogfood pass. Fresh packed install at /tmp/pm-context-proof-yZAk2N proved CLI context rebuilt->fresh reuse, next isolation, SDK index cursor access, derived_index provenance, and a 192-token bound."
  "2026-07-22T05:46:55.355Z",codex-root-20260722,"Review round 1 start: exact head 5693fda3 passed coverage, CodeQL, Semgrep, security, compatibility, runtime smoke, Windows, and benchmarks; CI exposed three strict lint findings and DeepScan reported two new findings. Reopened only this actively edited signal-layer item for the correction loop."
  "2026-07-22T05:50:50.259Z",codex-root-20260722,"PR #643 review round 1 fix: removed the two stale imports reported by exact-head static analysis/DeepScan and split the command integration scenario around a shared multi-use fixture so the strict complexity rule remains enabled. Focused command, SDK store, and derived-index suites pass 15/15; typecheck, ESLint, zero-clone duplication, 100% docstring/static quality, and diff checks pass."
  "2026-07-22T06:03:30.630Z",codex-root-20260722,"PR #643 review round 2: DeepScan is clean (0 new findings); exact 100% coverage, CodeQL, Semgrep, typecheck, smokes, compatibility, Windows, security, and benchmarks all passed. Static changelog validation correctly caught that daily release 2026.7.22 advanced main after this branch began; merged current main with the installed field-aware merge driver and regenerated CHANGELOG.md through pm-changelog 2026.7.18 against the combined tracker state."
  "2026-07-22T06:10:48.151Z",codex-root-20260722,"PR #643 static root cause correction: CI had fetched the newly published v2026.7.22 git tag and installed pm-changelog 2026.7.22, while the long-lived checkout lacked that tag and retained managed pm-changelog 2026.7.18. After fetching the PR merge ref/tags and explicitly upgrading through pm install, package generation adds the correct 2026.7.22 release boundary and check mode is deterministic. Isolated package doctor has zero blocking failures and runtime contracts expose changelog generate."
  "2026-07-22T06:16:56.961Z",codex-root-20260722,"PR #643 delayed review round start: CodeRabbit review 4751469967 arrived from head 24d95e73 after final CI. Verify positive-integer error parity, scale-adjusted fallback budget, and alleged claim contract drift against current contracts; accept only current valid findings and document any false positive."
  "2026-07-22T06:29:01.942Z",codex-root-20260722,"PR #643 delayed CodeRabbit review resolved with TDD: token-budget strings now share the positive-integer error contract for negative, fractional, and blank values; large-workspace context derives its default packing budget only after the full-depth limit is scale-adjusted; and pm claim --next now exposes and forwards --token-budget/--explain-ranking with hidden snake_case aliases, shell completions, strict CLI contracts, and generated snapshots to match SDK/MCP claim-next. Focused suite passes 229/229. Full suite passes 335 files / 6,080 tests with exact 100% statements (41,096/41,096), branches (28,941/28,941), functions (8,343/8,343), and lines (39,969/39,969). ESLint, zero-clone jscpd, build/typecheck, contracts, 100% docstrings/static quality, SDK package boundary, and token-budget gates pass."
notes[3]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-07T07:27:25.206Z",maintainer-agent,"Planning pass 2026-07-07: candidate additional derived signal — estimation calibration. estimated_minutes is a required metadata field but nothing compares it against actual duration derived from history streams (claim-to-close spans, cf. pm-pee5 flow metrics). Two uses: (a) ranking — items whose elapsed active time greatly exceeds estimate are aging-WIP risks worth surfacing; (b) planning — a per-author/per-type calibration factor makes future estimates and pm plan step budgeting evidence-based. Derivation belongs in this feature store; presentation belongs in pm-pee5."
  "2026-07-10T10:47:19.567Z",maintainer-agent,"Design constraints 2026-07-10 (planning pass, pre-implementation): the store MUST keep derived state strictly outside the immutable history chain. (a) Authoritative data = item files + history JSONL only; every store artifact is recomputable from them and carries the history cursor (per-stream entry hash/offset) it was folded up to — invalidation is cursor comparison, never mtime. (b) Write path: algorithm (6) write-time fold updates signals incrementally per mutation, O(1) amortized, behind the existing instant-mutation/background-refresh pattern (never blocks the mutating command). (c) Read path: signals serve pm context/next through the pm-h3no scorer contract's canonical signal shape; consumers never read store files directly. (d) Shared substrate with pm-801d: the persistent derived read index and this signal store are the same class of artifact (cursor-stamped derived read-path state); define ONE layout/versioning/invalidation convention (format_version-gated directory, e.g. .pm/derived/, gitignored) so pm-801d can land before or after without a contract change — this addresses the blocked_by edge either way. (e) Degradation: absent or stale store = recompute-on-demand scan fallback (correctness identical, latency worse), so small workspaces pay zero setup and corruption is self-healing (delete = full refold). (f) Signals are versioned: signal_set_version bump forces refold, enabling algorithm evolution without migrations. (g) Concurrency: single-writer fold via the existing lock discipline; readers get last-consistent snapshot (write-temp + atomic rename), no partial reads."
  "2026-07-13T17:50:38.081Z",maintainer-agent,"Fold-state ownership additions from pm-4k6b directed pass 2026-07-13 — three new algorithms land their write-time state in this store (wave 3, same event-sourced fold as algorithm (6), no daemon per ADR pm-i7i4): (20) temporal non-stationarity — change-point run-length state over population statistics (mutation rate, author-set Jaccard, vocabulary drift) + small era table + per-item ring-buffer binned access counts for periodicity; (21) hierarchical shrinkage — one evidence count n + prior pointer per folded statistic, conjugate closed-form blends, prior taxonomy item<-type<-workspace<-shipped defaults; (22) lineage continuity — kind-specific relevance mass transfer on terminal lineage events + identity-collapsed statistics (evidence sums along lineage chains, feeding (21)). Full definitions in the pm-4k6b notes ledger, algorithms (20)-(22)."
learnings[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-21T16:59:25.959Z",codex-derived-context-20260721,Derived feature stores should make freshness a caller-verifiable cursor contract and return cache status plus recovery warnings; hiding fallback behind an opaque cache makes correctness and latency impossible for SDK consumers to reason about.
